+-------------+
| UNDER LINUX |
+-------------+

Howto compile the files under Linux:

1. Obtain e install aclocal/autoconf/automake (google.com o gnu.org). It's free.
2. The first time, execute under command line and in the directory:
      aclocal
      autoconf
      automake -a
      ./configure
      gmake 
3. The next times, when you modify a source, only execute
      gmake
4. run the programs
      ./run.sh


+---------------+
| UNDER WINDOWS |
+---------------+

Howto compile the files under Windows:
1. Open the file GetDir.dsw with Visual Studio 6.0 (under Windows 2000), and build the 2 projects
3. Rename run_bat as run.bat
      move run_bat run.bat
2. run the programs
      run.bat

